# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  EXAMPLE ENV FILE — copy to .env and fill in. NEVER commit .env
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This file is for LOCAL DEVELOPMENT only (when running `wrangler pages dev`).
# In production, set these same vars in:
#   Cloudflare dashboard → your Pages project → Settings → Environment variables
#
# ─── Contact form (Resend) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Sign up free at https://resend.com (3,000 emails/month, no card)
# Dashboard → API Keys → Create API key → copy the `re_...` value

RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Where contact-form messages get delivered. Defaults to your iCloud if unset.
TO_EMAIL=chrisjasonmcqueen@icloud.com

# The "from" address shown in the email.
#  - If you haven't verified a domain in Resend yet: leave as onboarding@resend.dev
#  - Once you verify chrisjasonmcqueen.com in Resend: change to hello@chrisjasonmcqueen.com
FROM_EMAIL=onboarding@resend.dev


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  REFERENCE — services that DON'T need env vars
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Stripe Payment Links → paste URLs into src/data/products.ts
#   Each product has a `buyUrl` field. Format: https://buy.stripe.com/xxxxx
#   These are public links by design — safe to commit.
#
# Cal.com booking links → public URLs
#   Free intro call:  src/components/Nav.astro
#   $120 mentorship:  src/data/products.ts (mentorship-call.buyUrl)
#
# YouTube channel link → public URL in Nav.astro and footer
#
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  OPTIONAL — only if you add features later
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Plausible / Google Analytics — set ANALYTICS_ID and add the script tag
# ANALYTICS_ID=
#
# Stripe webhook secret (only if you build a webhook for auto-fulfillment)
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxxxx
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_xxxxx
#
# Decap CMS OAuth proxy (only if you self-host the proxy with secrets in your repo,
# which you shouldn't — secrets live in the Worker, not here)
